# u-forge.ai Project Structure Guide

Local-first TTRPG worldbuilding tool with AI-powered knowledge graphs. Built in Rust.

**Status:** Working prototype. CLI demo. Multi-crate Cargo workspace under `crates/`.

## Architecture Overview

Read [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:ARCHITECTURE.md) for full details (module map, SQLite schema, resolved bugs, design decisions).

## Workspace Layout

The project is a Cargo workspace. All crates live under `crates/`:

| Crate | Kind | Status | Purpose |
|-------|------|--------|---------|
| `u-forge-core` | lib | Complete | All current source (storage, AI, hardware, queue, search, schema, ingest) |
| `u-forge-graph-view` | lib | In Progress | Graph view model + layout engine (see `feature_UI.md`) |
| `u-forge-ui-traits` | lib | In Progress | Framework-agnostic rendering contracts (see `feature_UI.md`) |
| `u-forge-ui-gpui` | bin | In Progress | GPUI native app — pan/zoom canvas, LOD rendering (see `feature_UI.md`) |
| `u-forge-ui-egui` | bin | Skeleton | egui fallback — only if GPUI spike fails (spike passed; unlikely needed) |
| `u-forge-ts-runtime` | lib | Skeleton | Embedded deno_core TypeScript sandbox (see `feature_TS-Agent-Sandbox.md`) |

`defaults/` (schemas + sample data) lives at the **workspace root**, not inside any crate. `cli_demo.rs` resolves it via `env!("CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR") + "/../../defaults/"`.

## Current Architecture (u-forge-core)

- **Facade**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/lib.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/lib.rs) — `KnowledgeGraph` struct (owns storage + schemas). Bulk methods: `get_all_edges()`, `get_nodes_paginated(offset, limit)`.
- **Storage**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/graph/storage.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/graph/storage.rs) — SQLite via `rusqlite` (bundled). Tables: `nodes`, `edges`, `chunks`, `schemas` + FTS5 virtual table `chunks_fts` + sqlite-vec virtual tables `chunks_vec` (768-dim) and `chunks_vec_hq` (4096-dim). Key constants: `EMBEDDING_DIMENSIONS = 768`, `HIGH_QUALITY_EMBEDDING_DIMENSIONS = 4096`, `MAX_CHUNK_TOKENS = 350`.
- **Embeddings**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/embeddings.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/embeddings.rs) — `EmbeddingProvider` trait, `EmbeddingModelInfo`, `EmbeddingProviderType`. Implementation (`LemonadeProvider`) lives in `lemonade/embedding.rs`; re-exported here. No `EmbeddingManager`.
- **Transcription**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/transcription.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/transcription.rs) — `TranscriptionProvider` trait + `mime_for_filename()`. Implementation (`LemonadeTranscriptionProvider`) lives in `lemonade/transcription.rs`; re-exported here. No `TranscriptionManager`.
- **Application Config**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/config.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/config.rs) — `AppConfig`, `EmbeddingDeviceConfig`, `ModelConfig`, `ChatConfig`, `ChatDeviceConfig`, `ChatDevice`. TOML loading from `u-forge.toml`. `ModelConfig` holds per-model `load_params`, preference lists for model selection, `high_quality_embedding_models`. `ChatConfig` controls preferred device, per-device model overrides (`[chat.gpu]`, `[chat.npu]`), system prompt, RAG settings.
- **Inference Queue**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/queue/](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/queue) — `InferenceQueue` + `InferenceQueueBuilder` + `QueueStats`. Five capability channels: `WeightedEmbedDispatcher` (for embeddings), `transcribe_queue`, `synthesize_queue`, `generate_queue`, `rerank_queue`. Register providers via `.with_provider(BuiltProvider)`. Per-job retry: up to 3 attempts with exponential backoff.
- **Extended Lemonade Integration**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/lemonade/](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/lemonade) — Catalog-driven model discovery and provider construction:
  - `lemonade/catalog.rs` — `LemonadeServerCatalog` (fetches `/models`, `/system-info`, `/health` concurrently; `CatalogModel`, `LoadedModel`, `InstalledBackend`)
  - `lemonade/selector.rs` — `ModelSelector` (picks best downloaded model per capability/device slot; deduplicates to one worker per slot; `SelectedModel`, `QualityTier`; `model_by_id()` for exact lookup)
  - `lemonade/provider_factory.rs` — `ProviderFactory::build()` (constructs live providers from `SelectedModel`; `Capability`, `BuiltProvider`, `ProviderSlot`)
  - `lemonade/duplicate_guard.rs` — `DuplicateGuard` (detects duplicate llamacpp model names across backends)
  - `lemonade/embedding.rs` — `LemonadeProvider` (re-exported via `ai/embeddings.rs`)
  - `lemonade/transcription.rs` — `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` (re-exported via `ai/transcription.rs`)
  - `lemonade/gpu_manager.rs` — `GpuResourceManager`, `GpuWorkload`, `LlmGuard`, `SttGuard`
  - `lemonade/chat.rs` — `LemonadeChatProvider`, `ChatRequest`, `ChatMessage`, `ChatCompletionResponse`
  - `lemonade/stt.rs` — `LemonadeSttProvider`, `TranscriptionResult`
  - `lemonade/tts.rs` — `LemonadeTtsProvider`, `KokoroVoice`
  - `lemonade/rerank.rs` — `LemonadeRerankProvider`, `RerankDocument`
  - `lemonade/system_info.rs` — `SystemInfo`, `SystemDeviceInfo`, `RecipeBackendInfo`
  - `lemonade/load.rs` — `load_model()`, `ModelLoadOptions`
  - `lemonade/health.rs` — `LemonadeHealth`, `LoadedModelEntry`
- **Hybrid Search**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/search/](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/search) — `search_hybrid(graph, queue, query, config)` free async function. RRF merge of FTS5 + ANN (standard + HQ), optional rerank, graceful degradation.
- **Schemas**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/schema/](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/schema)
- **Data Import**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/ingest/data.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/ingest/data.rs) — JSONL two-pass import.

## Lemonade Integration

**Standard on [Lemonade Server](https://github.com/lemonade-sdk/lemonade)** (AMD, OpenAI-compatible API) for all AI:
- Model discovery: `GET /api/v1/models`, `GET /system-info`, `GET /health` — `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover(url)` fetches all three concurrently.
- Model selection: `ModelSelector::new(catalog, config)` — picks best downloaded model per capability/device slot, deduplicates to one provider per slot.
- Provider construction: `ProviderFactory::build(sel, capability, url, queue_depth, gpu_mgr, already_loaded)` — builds live providers from `SelectedModel`. Pass `catalog.loaded` IDs as `already_loaded` to skip the `/load` round-trip for models that are already running; pass `&[]` to always send the load request.
- Embeddings: `POST /api/v1/embeddings` — `LemonadeProvider` in `lemonade/embedding.rs`; re-exported via `ai::embeddings`.
- Transcription: `POST /api/v1/audio/transcriptions` — `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` (simple, no GPU lock) or `LemonadeSttProvider` (GPU-managed, shares `GpuResourceManager`).
- Reranking: `POST /api/v1/reranking` — `LemonadeRerankProvider`; wired into `InferenceQueue` via `rerank_queue`.
- Chat/LLM: `POST /api/v1/chat/completions` — `LemonadeChatProvider`; dispatched via `generate_queue` for GPU llamacpp and NPU FLM models.
- System info: `GET /system-info` — `SystemInfo::fetch()`; derives installed backends from recipe information.

**Hardware capability mapping** (derived from `/system-info`):

| Hardware | Recipes/Backends | Capabilities |
|---|---|---|
| AMD NPU (XDNA2) | FLM | `Embedding`, `Transcription`, `TextGeneration` |
| AMD iGPU (ROCm/Vulkan) | llamacpp:rocm, llamacpp:vulkan, whispercpp:vulkan | `Transcription`, `TextGeneration`, `Reranking`, `Embedding` (via GGUF) |
| CPU | kokoro, llamacpp (cpu) | `TextToSpeech`, `Embedding` (via GGUF) |

## Key Integration Points

The `EmbeddingProvider` trait in [crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/embeddings.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/embeddings.rs) is the primary abstraction for embedding work. The trait is dependency-free; `LemonadeProvider` (in `lemonade/embedding.rs`) is the only implementation. Do NOT bypass the trait.

The `TranscriptionProvider` trait in [crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/transcription.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/transcription.rs) is the primary abstraction for STT work. Both `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` (lemonade/transcription.rs — simple, no GPU lock) and `LemonadeSttProvider` (lemonade/stt.rs — GPU-managed) implement it. Do NOT bypass the trait.

**There is no `DeviceWorker` trait.** The hardware abstraction layer (`hardware/` module) was removed in the hardware refactor. Physical device differences are handled by `ModelSelector` (picks the right recipe/backend per device slot) and `ProviderFactory` (constructs the appropriate provider type). See `lemonade/selector.rs` and `lemonade/provider_factory.rs`.

For new code that needs embedding, transcription, TTS, LLM generation, or reranking: discover the catalog with `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover()`, select models with `ModelSelector`, build providers with `ProviderFactory::build()`, and register them with `InferenceQueueBuilder::with_provider()`. Do not call provider HTTP clients directly from business logic.

`LemonadeChatProvider` holds an `Option<Arc<GpuResourceManager>>`. `ProviderFactory` attaches the GPU manager automatically for llamacpp:rocm/vulkan/metal recipes and omits it for FLM (NPU) and kokoro (CPU) models.

`KnowledgeGraph` does **not** hold an `InferenceQueue` or any AI provider. Storage and schema operations are fully synchronous and require no running server. All AI capabilities are opt-in — construct them separately when needed.

## Integration Test Threading

Integration tests hit a shared live Lemonade Server. When `LEMONADE_URL` is set,
all modules' integration tests run concurrently by default, causing intermittent
GPU/NPU resource contention on the server side.

**Always run the full test suite with `--test-threads=1` when `LEMONADE_URL` is set.**
`dev.sh` sets this flag automatically when it detects `LEMONADE_URL` in the environment.

```bash
# Correct — single-threaded to avoid server contention
LEMONADE_URL=http://localhost:13305/api/v1 cargo test -- --test-threads=1

# dev.sh handles this automatically
export LEMONADE_URL=http://localhost:13305/api/v1
./dev.sh --backend-only
```

