## ModelSelector Device Slots

`ModelSelector` assigns each downloaded model a **device slot** that determines deduplication:
- `flm` recipe → slot `"npu"`
- `llamacpp` + `rocm`/`vulkan`/`metal` backend → slot `"gpu"`
- `llamacpp` + cpu or no backend → slot `"cpu"`
- other recipes (e.g. `whispercpp`, `kokoro`) → slot = recipe name

At most one provider is built per slot per quality tier (for embeddings) or per slot (for LLM/STT). `model_by_id(id, quality_tier)` bypasses preference lists for exact-ID lookups (used by `cli_chat` to honour `[chat.gpu]`/`[chat.npu]` config overrides).
